11:50:47 AM [express] GET /api/admin/portfolio-memory 200 in 613ms :: [{"recordId":1,"id":"identity","order":1,"title":"Who Klein Lavina Is","eyebrow":"Portfolio Snapshot","summary":"Klein F. Lavina is a fresh graduate from the Philippines building full-stack web apps with Django, PHP, React, and PostgreSQL.","context":"This is the top-level identity block the assistant should use before diving into projects, skills, or contact details.","accent":"primary","facts":[{"label":"Role","value":"Fresh Graduate / Full Stack Developer"},{"label":"Location","value":"Philippines"},{"label":"Status","value":"Open to work"},{"label":"Certification","value":"PhilNITS Passer"}],"items":["Built 8+ portfolio-relevant projects.","Works across school, internship, and personal project contexts.","Prefers practical builds that mirror real workflows."],"links":[],"isActive":true,"createdAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00","updatedAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00"},{"recordId":2,"id":"about","order":2,"title":"How Klein Describes His Work","eyebrow":"Narrative","summary":"Klein focuses on understanding how websites really work under the surface and prefers shipping useful systems over polishing empty demos.","context":"Use this when the question is about personality, motivation, working style, or the voice behind the portfolio.","accent":"secondary","facts":[],"items":["He cares about code that makes sense to the next person reading it.","He is still actively learning, experimenting, and refining each version.","He values clarity over pretending to know everything.","Signature line: 'Passed PhilNITS. Still googling CSS flexbox.'"],"links":[],"isActive":true,"createdAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00","updatedAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00"},{"recordId":3,"id":"values","order":3,"title":"Values Behind The Builds","eyebrow":"Working Principles","summary":"The portfolio is grounded in clean code, honesty, shipping, constant learning, and iteration.","context":"Use this when a recruiter or visitor asks how Klein works, what he prioritizes, or what makes his approach dependable.","accent":"accent","facts":[],"items":["Clean Code - write it so someone else can read it tomorrow.","Honesty - say 'I don't know yet' instead of faking certainty.","Ship It - done and imperfect beats perfect and never shipped.","Always Learning - every bug is a lesson.","Iteration - version 1 is never the final version."],"links":[],"isActive":true,"createdAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00","updatedAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00"},{"recordId":4,"id":"technical-skills","order":4,"title":"Technical Skills And Tools","eyebrow":"Technical Arsenal","summary":"Klein's stack spans frontend, backend, databases, languages, and day-to-day tooling used across modern web projects.","context":"Use this when the question is about stack coverage, strongest technologies, or whether Klein can handle full-stack work.","accent":"primary","facts":[],"items":["Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, TypeScript, React, Next.js, Tailwind, Bootstrap.","Backend: Django, PHP.","Databases: MySQL, PostgreSQL.","Languages: Java, Python, R.","Tools: VS Code, Git, GitHub, Figma, Postman, Cloudinary, Replit, Render, Canva."],"links":[],"isActive":true,"createdAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00","updatedAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00"},{"recordId":5,"id":"soft-skills","order":5,"title":"Soft Skills And Collaboration Strengths","eyebrow":"Professional Skills","summary":"Beyond the tech stack, Klein emphasizes problem solving, teamwork, troubleshooting, adaptability, continuous learning, and communication.","context":"Use this when a visitor is evaluating work style, collaboration fit, or reliability on a team.","accent":"secondary","facts":[],"items":["Problem Solving - analytical approach to complex challenges.","Team Collaboration - effective communication and teamwork.","Technical Troubleshooting - fast diagnosis and resolution.","Adaptability - quick to learn new tools and workflows.","Communication - clear with both technical and non-technical people."],"links":[],"isActive":true,"createdAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00","updatedAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00"},{"recordId":6,"id":"projects","order":6,"title":"Project Catalog With Context","eyebrow":"Featured Work","summary":"The project list should be treated as ordered work history showing progression from practical systems to chatbots, CMS builds, and e-commerce platforms.","context":"Use this when the question is about specific projects, recent work, stack choices, live demos, or GitHub references.","accent":"accent","facts":[],"items":["01. RDFS - Real-time Dispatch and Finance System - Capstone project focused on real-world transport operations, finance flow, and live dispatch visibility. Stack: JavaScript, Django, HTML, CSS, PostgreSQL, Bootstrap, Cloudinary, OnRender.","02. WISE-PENRO - Work Indicator Submission Engine - Workflow-driven system shaped by how staff actually submit and process documents day to day. Stack: Django, PostgreSQL, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Cloudinary, OnRender, Brevo SMTP.","03. J-Gear Assistant Chatbot - Portfolio-relevant chatbot work that connects directly to Klein's interest in structured conversational UX. Stack: TypeScript, React, CSS, HTML, Vite, Netlify.","04. Tag-os Elementary School Website - Shows Klein's ability to build content-managed interfaces instead of static brochure pages. Stack: React, JavaScript, CSS, Vite, HTML, Netlify.","05. Cracken Gear Fits - A third-year project that moved from school requirements into a usable deployed build. Stack: PHP, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, MySQL, InfinityFree.","06. Cracken Furniture - A second variation of Klein's original e-commerce design, adapted for a classmate while retaining authorship. Stack: PHP, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, MySQL, InfinityFree."],"links":[{"url":"https://rdfsmaasin.onrender.com","label":"RDFS - Real-time Dispatch and Finance System Live"},{"url":"https://github.com/KleinLavina/RDFS","label":"RDFS - Real-time Dispatch and Finance System GitHub"},{"url":"https://r8penrowise.onrender.com","label":"WISE-PENRO - Work Indicator Submission Engine Live"},{"url":"https://github.com/KleinLavina/WISE-PENRO","label":"WISE-PENRO - Work Indicator Submission Engine GitHub"},{"url":"https://jgeartatakjosephinian.netlify.app/","label":"J-Gear Assistant Chatbot Live"},{"url":"https://github.com/KleinLavina/J-Gear-Chatbot","label":"J-Gear Assistant Chatbot GitHub"},{"url":"https://tagoselementary.netlify.app/","label":"Tag-os Elementary School Website Live"},{"url":"https://github.com/KleinLavina/TES","label":"Tag-os Elementary School Website GitHub"},{"url":"https://cgearfits.rf.gd/","label":"Cracken Gear Fits Live"},{"url":"https://github.com/KleinLavina/CrackenGearFits","label":"Cracken Gear Fits GitHub"},{"url":"https://cfurniture.rf.gd/","label":"Cracken Furniture Live"},{"url":"https://github.com/KleinLavina/CrackenFurnture","label":"Cracken Furniture GitHub"}],"isActive":true,"createdAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00","updatedAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00"},{"recordId":7,"id":"timeline","order":7,"title":"Developer Journey In Order","eyebrow":"Growth Timeline","summary":"The timeline explains how Klein progressed from early web fundamentals into systems design, deployed projects, and the modern stack.","context":"Use this when the user asks about experience level, progression, learning path, or how Klein grew over time.","accent":"primary","facts":[],"items":["2022 - The First Line: Klein started BSIT at Saint Joseph College and began learning HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and basic Java programming.","2023 - The Architect Phase: The focus shifted from syntax to systems thinking through data flow diagrams, database design, and relational modeling.","2024 - Building Real Things: Theory turned into deployed work through live e-commerce builds, paid project delivery, and first hosting experience.","2025 - The Modern Stack: Klein moved into React, Vite, and Django while shipping chatbot work, capstone systems, and school-focused CMS builds."],"links":[],"isActive":true,"createdAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00","updatedAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00"},{"recordId":8,"id":"contact","order":8,"title":"How To Reach Klein","eyebrow":"Contact","summary":"Klein is open to project inquiries, quick questions, and collaboration through email, GitHub, Facebook, or the portfolio contact form.","context":"Use this when the user asks how to contact Klein, what to include in an inquiry, or where to verify identity.","accent":"secondary","facts":[{"label":"Primary Email","value":"kleinlavina@gmail.com"},{"label":"Alternate Email In QR","value":"kleinlav7@gmail.com"},{"label":"Phone","value":"+639380734878"},{"label":"Preferred Route","value":"Portfolio form or direct email"}],"items":["GitHub: https://github.com/KleinLavina","Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/klein.lavina.12","Best for hiring and project inquiries: send a short scope, timeline, and preferred contact method."],"links":[{"url":"https://github.com/KleinLavina","label":"GitHub"},{"url":"https://www.facebook.com/klein.lavina.12","label":"Facebook"}],"isActive":true,"createdAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00","updatedAt":"2026-03-18T03:50:31.953566+00:00"}]
